Section 1:
1 L.D. 1629
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1083, L.D. 1629, “An Act to Require
10 Legislative Committees to Provide Equal Time to Each Member of the Public Who
11 Testifies”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 3 MRSA §165, sub-§9 is enacted to read:
15 9. Testimony before committees. During a public hearing, each member of the public
16 providing testimony before the committee must be allowed the same amount of time to
17 testify. Once a public hearing has begun, the amount of time set for the first member of
18 the public providing testimony must be allowed for each following member of the public
19 providing testimony until the conclusion of the hearing.'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, clarifies that once a
2244 public hearing has begun, the amount of time set for the first member of the public
2255 providing testimony must be allowed for each following member of the public providing
2266 testimony until the conclusion of the hearing.
2277 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2288 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR2194(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
